38 //
39 // Base class for all planners. Planners are templated on state and dynamics
40 // types **of the planner** NOT **of the tracker,** as well as the tracking
41 // error bound type and environment. Planners take in start and goal states, and
42 // start time, and output a trajectory of planner states.
43 //
44 // Templated on state (S), environment (E), dynamics (D), dynamics service (SD),
45 // bound (B), and bound service (SB).
46 //

65 template<typename S, typename E,
66  typename D, typename SD, typename B, typename SB>
67 class Planner {
68 public:
69  virtual ~Planner() {}
70 
71  // Initialize from a ROS NodeHandle.
72  bool Initialize(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
73 
74 protected:
75  explicit Planner()
76  : initialized_(false) {}
77 
78  // Load parameters and register callbacks. These may be overridden
79  // by derived classes if needed (they should still call these functions
80  // via Planner::LoadParameters and Planner::RegisterCallbacks).
81  virtual bool LoadParameters(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
82  virtual bool RegisterCallbacks(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
83 
84  // Callback to handle replanning requests.
85  inline void ReplanRequestCallback(
86  const fastrack_msgs::ReplanRequest::ConstPtr& msg) const {
87  // Unpack start/stop states.
88  const S start(msg->start);
89  const S goal(msg->goal);
90 
91  // Plan and publish.
92  traj_pub_.publish(Plan(start, goal, msg->start_time).ToRos());
93  }
94 
95  // Plan a trajectory from the given start to goal states starting
96  // at the given time.
97  virtual Trajectory<S> Plan(
98  const S& start, const S& goal, double start_time=0.0) const = 0;
99 
100  // Keep a copy of the dynamics, tracking bound, and environment.
101  D dynamics_;
102  B bound_;
103  E env_;
104 
105  // Max amount of time for planning to run each time.
106  double max_runtime_;
107 
108  // Publisher and subscriber.
109  ros::Subscriber replan_request_sub_;
110  ros::Publisher traj_pub_;
111 
112  std::string replan_request_topic_;
113  std::string traj_topic_;
114 
115  // Services for loading dynamics and bound.
116  ros::ServiceClient dynamics_srv_;
117  ros::ServiceClient bound_srv_;
118 
119  std::string dynamics_srv_name_;
120  std::string bound_srv_name_;
121 
122  // Naming and initialization.
123  std::string name_;
124  bool initialized_;
125 }; //\class Planner

129 // Initialize from a ROS NodeHandle.
130 template<typename S, typename E,
131  typename D, typename SD, typename B, typename SB>
132 bool Planner<S, E, D, SD, B, SB>::Initialize(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
133  name_ = ros::names::append(n.getNamespace(), "Planner");
134 
135  if (!LoadParameters(n)) {
136  ROS_ERROR("%s: Failed to load parameters.", name_.c_str());
137  return false;
138  }
139 
140  if (!RegisterCallbacks(n)) {
141  ROS_ERROR("%s: Failed to register callbacks.", name_.c_str());
142  return false;
143  }
144 
145  // Initialize environment.
146  if (!env_.Initialize(n)) {
147  ROS_ERROR("%s: Failed to initialize environment.", name_.c_str());
148  return false;
149  }
150 
151  // Set bound by calling service provided by tracker.
152  if (!bound_srv_) {
153  ROS_ERROR("%s: Bound server was disconnected.", name_.c_str());
154  return false;
155  }
156 
157  SB b;
158  if (!bound_srv_.call(b)) {
159  ROS_ERROR("%s: Bound server error.", name_.c_str());
160  return false;
161  }
162 
163  bound_.FromRos(b.response);
164 
165  // Set dynamics by calling service provided by tracker.
166  if (!dynamics_srv_) {
167  ROS_ERROR("%s: Dynamics server was disconnected.", name_.c_str());
168  return false;
169  }
170 
171  SD d;
172  if (!dynamics_srv_.call(d)) {
173  ROS_ERROR("%s: Dynamics server error.", name_.c_str());
174  return false;
175  }
176 
177  dynamics_.FromRos(d.response);
178 
179  initialized_ = true;
180  return true;
181 }
182 
183 // Load parameters.
184 template<typename S, typename E,
185  typename D, typename SD, typename B, typename SB>
186 bool Planner<S, E, D, SD, B, SB>::LoadParameters(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
187  ros::NodeHandle nl(n);
188 
189  // Topics.
190  if (!nl.getParam("topics/traj", traj_topic_)) return false;
191  if (!nl.getParam("topics/replan_request", replan_request_topic_))
192  return false;
193 
194  // Services.
195  if (!nl.getParam("srvs/dynamics", dynamics_srv_name_)) return false;
196  if (!nl.getParam("srvs/bound", bound_srv_name_)) return false;
197 
198  // Max runtime per call.
199  if (!nl.getParam("max_runtime", max_runtime_)) return false;
200 
201  return true;
202 }
203 
204 // Register callbacks.
205 template<typename S, typename E,
206  typename D, typename SD, typename B, typename SB>
207 bool Planner<S, E, D, SD, B, SB>::RegisterCallbacks(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
208  ros::NodeHandle nl(n);
209 
210  // Subscribers.
211  replan_request_sub_ = nl.subscribe(
212  replan_request_topic_.c_str(), 1, &Planner::ReplanRequestCallback, this);
213 
214  // Publishers.
215  traj_pub_ = nl.advertise<fastrack_msgs::Trajectory>(
216  traj_topic_.c_str(), 1, false);
217 
218  // Services.
219  ros::service::waitForService(dynamics_srv_name_);
220  dynamics_srv_ = nl.serviceClient<SD>(dynamics_srv_name_.c_str(), true);
221 
222  ros::service::waitForService(bound_srv_name_);
223  bound_srv_ = nl.serviceClient<SB>(bound_srv_name_.c_str(), true);
224 
225  return true;
226 }
